Class ProtobufUtils

    Utilities for proto3

    This does not support the following field types: Any. This does not support any extensions. This also ignores any declared services.

      • buildRowValues

        public static List<Object> buildRowValues(Descriptors.Descriptor dsc,
                                          Message msg,
                                          StructType schema)
        Retrieves and converts Protobuf fields from a Message.

        If the field in the Descriptors.Descriptor exists in the Message, the value is retrieved and converted using getFieldValue(Descriptors.FieldDescriptor, Object, DataType). Otherwise, the field value is null. The extraction honors the order of the Descriptor.

        Parameters:
        dsc - the Protobuf Descriptor with all fields
        msg - the Message with the current field values
        schema - the Dataset schema derived from the Descriptor
        Returns:
        a list of converted values

      • buildSchema

        public static StructType buildSchema(Descriptors.Descriptor descriptor)
        Construct a Dataset schema from a Descriptor

        This iterates and recurses through a Descriptors.Descriptor and produces a StructType for Dataset<Row>. Protobuf oneof fields are flattened into discrete StructField instances.

        This will pass the value of Descriptors.FieldDescriptor#isRequired() to the associated StructField.

        Parameters:
        descriptor - the Descriptor to convert
        Returns:
        the converted StructType

      • buildDescriptor

        public static Descriptors.Descriptor buildDescriptor(String filePath,
                                                     String messageName)
        Constructs a named Message from a .desc file into a Descriptor.

        This will parse the .desc file and then extract the encapsulated Descriptors.Descriptor the designated Message from the resulting parent Descriptors.FileDescriptor.

        Parameters:
        filePath - the location of the .desc file
        messageName - the name of the Message
        Returns:
        the constructed Descriptor
